  "abstract": "The Board is amending its Regulation A to establish a special lending program under which Federal Reserve Banks will extend credit at a rate 150 basis points above the Federal Open Market Committee's targeted federal funds rate to eligible institutions to accommodate liquidity needs during the century date change period. Unlike adjustment credit, borrowers will not be required to seek credit elsewhere first, uses of funds will not be limited, and the loans may be outstanding for any period while",
